text: Zadar County is a county in Croatia. The county seat is Zadar. The Velebit, Telaščica and Paklenica national parks are in the south of the county. ==Administrative division== Zadar County is divided into: * City ** Zadar * Towns ** Benkovac ** Biograd na Moru ** Nin ** Obrovac ** Pag * Municipalities ** Bibinje ** Galovac ** Gračac ** Jasenice ** Kali ** Kolan (since 2003) ** Kruševo ** Kukljica ** Lišane Ostrovičke ** Novigrad ** Pakoštane ** Pašman ** Petrčane ** Polača ** Poličnik ** Posedarje ** Povljane ** Preko ** Privlaka ** Ražanac ** Sali ** Stankovci ** Starigrad ** Sukošan ** Sveti Filip i Jakov ** Škabrnja ** Tkon ** Vir ** Vrsi ** Zemunik Donji ==References== Category:Counties of Croatia
